# Narrate Thinking — Speak Reasoning Before Redaction

Cursor redacts extended-thinking content once the thinking tab closes. **Speak the reasoning out loud** in speakable chunks before Cursor touches the transcript.

## When this applies

Every time you do significant internal reasoning — **speak the key reasoning out loud**.

This is NOT the acknowledgement nor the completion summary. This is the **middle part**.

## How to do it

**Prefer combining with the ack.** Fold short reasoning into the ack call from `acknowledge-before-planning.mdc`.

Only fire a **separate** thinking call when the reasoning is substantial (5+ sentences) and would make the ack awkwardly long.

### Singleton pattern

Thinking mode uses a **singleton lock** on the server. Only one thinking narration at a time — extras exit silently.

### Chunk rules

- **One chunk per message.** Three to six sentences.
- **Fire in the same parallel batch** as work tool calls — `block_until_ms: 0`.
- **Speak like a person thinking aloud.**
- **Cover reasoning, not actions** the thinking-sounds rule already covers.

### Template

```bash
$OPENCLAW_HOME/scripts/oc-speak.sh "So looking at this, I think the issue is [insight], because [reason]. The approach I would take is [plan]. One thing to be careful about is [risk]." 1 "" thinking
```

### Subagent variant

```bash
$OPENCLAW_HOME/scripts/oc-speak.sh "So I think the approach here is [reasoning]." 1 subagent thinking
```

## What to include in reasoning chunks

| Reasoning type | What to speak |
|----------------|---------------|
| Diagnosis | "I think the problem is X because Y" |
| Decision | "There are two ways — A or B. Going with A because..." |
| Discovery | "I found that X is actually doing Y, which means..." |
| Risk | "One thing that could go wrong is X, so I will..." |
| Architecture | "This needs X, Y, and Z. The order matters because..." |
| Debugging | "The error points to X, but I suspect Y upstream" |

## What NOT to do

- Do not dump twenty lines of internal monologue — distill.
- Do not block on speak calls.
- Do not repeat the acknowledgement phrasing.
- Do not fire multiple thinking chunks — combine into one paragraph.

## Ordering in a message

**Preferred (one speak call):**

```
Shell: oc-speak.sh "Got it. So the issue is [reasoning]. I will [plan]." 1
Read / Grep / Glob: actual work
```

**Long reasoning (two calls max):**

```
Shell: oc-speak.sh "Got it..." 1
Shell: oc-speak.sh "So the issue..." 1 "" thinking
Read / Grep / Glob: parallel
```

**Hard cap: never more than 2 speak calls per message (ack + thinking).**

## Gating

Respect `FRIDAY_CURSOR_NARRATION` from `.env` — see `cursor-agent-narration.mdc`.

## CRITICAL: You are the ONLY source of thinking narration

The watcher cannot capture thinking from JSONL. **`oc-speak.sh` with thinking mode is the ONLY way the user hears you think.**

## Why this matters

Speaking preserves reasoning as audio in real time before redaction removes it from the transcript.
